  "commentary": "With SPX at 6558.92 sitting directly between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-19.7B) and positive gamma resistance at 6580 (+8.7B), dealers are caught in aggressive hedging mode - they're likely buying this rally into 6580 where they'll turn heavy sellers. The breakout regime with -66.5B total GEX means any breach above 6580 should see explosive upside acceleration as dealers chase, while a break below 6550 triggers amplified selling pressure through the stacked negative gamma levels at 6545/6540. Watch 6550 as the critical support - a break there activates the negative gamma cascade, while 6580 is the key resistance where dealer selling pressure maxes out.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550-6580 with explosive moves on any breakout from this range.",
